The main thing that causes mage supports to be the issue they currently are is this item:

{{item:3303}} 

It (and its upgrades) have the highest gold generation of all support items - and said gold generation is tied to something mage supports want to do anyway, namely attacking the enemy. Moreover, the item also improves said attacking in a major way.

>Anyway, I played Leona AD mid like an idiot thinking I needed to buy a sword, shield, armor, boots, necklace and sunfire cap facepalm.

{{item:3078}} 
{{item:3143}} 
{{item:3083}} 
{{item:3107}} 
{{item:3068}} 
{{item:3158}} 

...

Looks viable to me, just drop the shield for something with MR for when you aren't playing an all AD team.
